        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 4:38PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 438 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Millers Creek Reservoir, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elbert and Us-183 Near The Throckmorton-Baylor County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
